sections.PROJECT:
- A Shear wall is provided in a building to resist seismic a wind forces.
This wall generally starts at foundation level and are continuous throughout the total height of building.
They are usually provided in between columns lines, in stair wells,lift wells and in shafts that house other utilities.
Shear wall provide lateral load resistance by transferring the wind and earthquake load to the foundation. Besides they 
impart lateral stiffness to the system and also carry gravity loads.
